<br>
Quest is basically:  Get Warmly+ with Priests of Nife in Qeynos.<br>
<br>
Camp two versions of Lord Grimrot in SK, (live and undead) which if you know the techniques can be partially painless, but also can be a  week's worth of sitting.<br>
<br>
That's not a problem.  The problem lies in the warmly faction required.<br>
<br>
There are three schools of thought:<br>
<br>
1. Murder Bloodsabres.  Handy, since a bunch of them hang out around Grimrot's camp, and if you know which one NOT to kill you can still get him to show.  This takes time, and ruins your Bloodsabre faction, which IS the design of the quest, but you can ruin it before you get Priests of Nife high enough, which leaves a few clerics without a guild.<br>
<br>
2.  Hand gold into Rosaeger Thusten (or whatever his name is.)  I don't know about you, but picking up 2 gold at a time to get faction is time consuming and a waste of my money, but I've seen it done...<br>
<br>
3.  Bandit sashes.  Herein lies the problem.  Unless you start on them when they're not trivial, you can't exactly go around murdering bandits when you're ready to do this quest, because their sashes are Magic.  Best method, grab some good money and experience, and the faction's incredible after about 200 of them (which is about maybe 500 platinum)<br>
<br>
